Join the Conversation To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Prep volleyball roundup: Tech rallies to top Alexandria TIMES STAFF REPORT 10:49 p.m. CDT October 22, 2015 Volleyball (Photo: Times graphic) 
ALEXANDRIA — After dropping the first two games, St. Cloud Tech rallied to win three straight and defeated Alexandria 3-2 in Central Lakes Conference prep volleyball action Thursday night. 
Game scores were 20-25, 21-25, 27-25, 26-24, 18-16. 
“There are no words to express how wonderful this feels,” said Tigers coach Kristy Husen, whose team is now 12-12 overall. “We just never game up and we stayed positive and that made the difference.” 
Paige Fashant and Kate Martig each had 15 kills. Kate Knowles had nine kills and five ace blocks. Martig added four blocks. 
ST. CLOUD APOLLO 3, FERGUS FALLS 0 
FERGUS FALLS — Lexie Hiltner had 11 kills to lead St. Cloud Apollo past Fergus Falls in Central Lakes Conference action. 
ROCORI 3, SAUK RAPIDS 0 
COLD SPRING — Eleanor Holthaus led Rocori with 14 kills with two blocks in a sweep of Sauk Rapids. 
Game scores were 25-11, 25-22, 25-19. 
Morgan Holthaus added 23 set assists and three blocks, Breanna Schouviller had 10 kills and Abby Templin finished with seven kills and 16 digs for the eighth-ranked Spartans, who finish the regular season 12-0 in the Central Lakes and 25-1 overall. 
Senior middle hitter Kyra Harvey had 12 kills to lead the Storm and Morgan Held added 15 set assists for Sauk Rapids (15-11). 
BRAINERD 3, SARTELL 0 
BRAINERD — Jaden Turner finished with six kills in Sartell’s loss to Brainerd. 
Game scores were 25-16, 25-15, 25-21. Ailsa Watson finished with 22 set assists and 14 digs for the Sabres. 
Granite Ridge 
ALBANY 3, LITTLE FALLS 1 
ALBANY — Erin Navratil had 27 kills and 11 digs as Albany wrapped up the Granite Ridge Conference title with a win over Little Falls. 
Game scores were 23-25, 25-19, 25-11, 25-14. Valerie Parker had 50 set assists and 14 digs. Courtney Buerman added 12 kills and Rachel Buttweiler had nine. 
Melanie Dorn had 14 kills and 12 set assists to lead the Flyers. 
ST. CLOUD CATHEDRAL 3, FOLEY 0 
Katie Auger led St. Cloud Cathedral had seven kills and four ace serves to lead St. Cloud Cathedral past Foley in Granite Ridge Conference action at Cathedral High School. 
Game scores were 25-9, 25-11, 25-16. 
Morgan Prom had 25 set assists for the Crusaders (19-7), three ace serves and 12 digs with six kills each from Sam Laudenbach and Megan Zniewski. 
BECKER 3, MORA 0 
BECKER — Kalie Jergens had 12 kills and Kalley Anderson added 10 as Becker beat Mora in Granite Ridge Conference action. 
Game scores were 25-22, 25-17, 25-12. 
Daisy Kent had 15 set assists. Jergens added nine digs and Anderson had four blocks. Alexa Hanowski had 17 digs. 
MILACA 3, ZIMMERMAN 0 
MILACA — Milaca cruised past Zimmerman in Granite Ridge Conference action. 
Central Minnesota 
PAYNESVILLE 3, HOLDINGFORD 0 
PAYNESVILLE — Ashley Froelich had a team-high 10 kills to lead the Bulldogs to a Central Minnesota Conference win over the Huskers. 
Game scores were 25-21, 25-20, 25-21. 
Katelyn Dingmann added nine kills for Paynesville. 
B-B-E 3, PIERZ 2 
PIERZ — Ashley Trustheim had 22 kills for Belgrade-Brooten-Elrosa in a Central Minnesota Conference win Thursday. 
Game scores were 25-8, 25-14, 24-26, 21-25, 15-9. 
BreAnna Hopkins had 12 set assists and 20 digs for Pierz. 
MAPLE LAKE 3, HL-W-W 1 
HOWARD LAKE — Olivia Marquette was 25-for-26 serving with four aces and 31 set assists to lead the Irish to a Central Minnesota Conference win over Howard Lake-Waverly-Winsted. 
Mollie Scheiber added eight kills for Maple Lake (6-1, 22-6). 
West Central 
SAUK CENTRE 3, MORRIS 1 
SAUK CENTRE — Becca Weir finished with 21 kills as Sauk Centre defeated Morris. 
Game scores were 25-22, 28-30, 25-15, 25-20. 
Jill Klaphake added nine kills with 21 digs and three ace serves. 
MELROSE 3, A-C-GC 0 
MELROSE — Hannah Wilner had five kills and Kendra Miller had four kills and three blocks, but Atwater-Cosmos-Grove City fell to Melrose. 
Game scores were 25-12, 25-14, 25-14. The Dutchmen improved to 19-10 overall. 
Wright County 
GLENCOE-SILVER LAKE 3, ANNANDALE 1 
ANNANDALE — Senior outside hitter Morgan Olson had 16 kills for the Cardinals in a Wright County Conference loss to the Panthers. 
Game scores were 26-24, 22-25, 25-14, 25-21. 
Kamryn D'Heilly added 12 kills and Karissa Peterson tallied 21 digs for Annandale (20-7). 
Christian Athletic 
ST. CLOUD CHRISTIAN 3, VALLEY CHRISTIAN (Wis.) 1 
ST. CROIX FALLS, Wis. — Leanna Murphy had five kills and 22 digs to lead St. Cloud Christian past Valley Christian. 
Game scores were 25-21, 25-14, 18-25, 25-22. 
Ellie Petrie added 22 digs for the Warriors. 
Nonconference 
KIMBALL — The host Cubs rolled past Upsala in nonconference action. 
Game scores were 25-8, 25-17, 25-3. 
G-F-W 3, EDEN VALLEY-WATKINS 1 
WINTHROP — Madeliene Geislinger led Eden Valley-Watkins with seven kills in a loss at Gibbon-Fairfax-Winthrop. 
Game scores were 25-16, 20-25, 25-12, 26-24. 
Noelle Hess added 32 digs for the Eagles (8-14). Read or Share this story: http://www.sctimes.com/story/sports/high-school/2015/10/22/prep-volleyball-roundup-tech-rallies-top-alexandria/74441004/ TOP VIDEOS
